<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strlen(hdr_value.str) is invoked without any prior, provable guarantee that the object pointed to by hdr_value.str contains a terminating NUL within its allocated bounds. If get_req_header returns a pointer/length pair where the buffer is not NUL-terminated (or the NUL lies beyond the allocated object), strlen will scan past the object's bounds looking for '\0', leading to a buffer over-read.
</scenario>

